<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="25" type="nomenclatural notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Nomenclatural notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="25">
When describing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vahl" authorityYear="1805" class="Liliopsida" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="Heteranthera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heteranthera diversifolia" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diversifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Heteranthera diversifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vahl, MH" journalOrPublisher="Hauniae, Impenis auctoris &amp; prostat apud J. H. Schubothe" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" refId="B118" refString="Vahl, MH, 1805. Enumeratio Plantarum, vel ab aliis, vel ab ipso observatarum, cum differentiis specificis, synonymis selectis et descriptionibus succinctis, vol. 2. Hauniae, Impenis auctoris &amp; prostat apud J.H. Schubothe" title="Enumeratio Plantarum, vel ab aliis, vel ab ipso observatarum, cum differentiis specificis, synonymis selectis et descriptionibus succinctis, vol. 2." year="1805">Vahl (1805)</bibRefCitation>
makes no direct mention of any analysed specimens in which he might have based the description of his new species. The author only mentions that his new species is native to Guiana and was sent to him by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Richard”">&quot;Richard&quot;</normalizedToken>
. After analysing the collection at C, we came across a specimen part of Herb. Vahlian., collected by 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">Richard s.n.</emphasis>
and identified in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Vahl’s">Vahl's</normalizedToken>
handwriting as 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Haemodoraceae" genus="H." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. diversifolia" order="Commelinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="25" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="diversifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="25">H. diversifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, it is chosen by us as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
